comment:
The restrooms are available to anyone during the library's open hours:

Monday: 9:00 am - 9:00 pm
Tuesday: 9:00 am - 9:00 pm
Wednesday: 9:00 am - 9:00 pm
Thursday: 9:00 am - 9:00 pm
Friday: 9:00 am - 6:00 pm
Saturday: 9:00 am - 1:00 pm
Sunday: Closed

name: University of Wisconsin Sheboygan Campus
directions: Go in through the main entrance. Turn left. Pass the rooms whose numbers begin with a three. Left again at the end of the hall. Go past the cafeteria through two sets of glass doors. The restroom is by the offices. It is in the hallway that joins the science building and main building together. You should see room numbers that start with a five.
comment: The university is a public building and is open to everyone until 10:00 PM. It is generally not a hostile environment for MOGAI people and the bathroom became gender neutral due to the efforts of the campus GSA. It is a single stall bathroom and very spacious.

comment:
The building is part of the university in Erlangen, but usually there should be no problem for anyone to use it.
It is marked as a restroom for men and women, but only for one person at a time, so anyone can use it, no matter how they identify.

comment: You can probably get away with using the restroom without buying anything. There's usually a lot of people so the people at the register probably won't notice you. Just get it, use the bathroom, get out.

name: Fry's Grocery Store
directions: All the way to the left of the store when you enter. Right next to the Pharmacy area, under the giant sign that says "Pharmacy", You'll see a sign that says "Restroom". There is a bathroom labeled "unisex" right next to the "men" and "women" restrooms.It is a single toilet bathroom, so there is a sign on the handle that says whether the restroom is vacant or not. Lock the door while you are using the bathroom to have the door handle display as "non-vacant"
comment: You don't have to buy anything; you can just get it, use the bathroom, and leave. The inside of the bathroom consists of a single toilet, sink, soap dispenser, baby changing table, trash can, mirror, and paper towel dispenser. Make sure to lock the door while using the restroom.

name: Hannaford Supermarket, 295 Forest Avenue, Portland, ME 04101, USA
directions: Family Restroom

name: Habana Inn
directions: Main lobby, and near Copa and finish Line clubs.
comment: No where in the Southwest will you find a place like the Habana Inn. With 170 hotel rooms, two swimming pools, two nightclubs, a restaurant, piano bar, and a unique gift shop all conveniently located within the hotel complex, the Habana Inn is the place to be. Room rates are affordable and weekly and monthly rates are available for extended stays. Leave your car parked for your entire stay as the complex is located in the heart of Oklahoma City's gay district. Six more clubs and several restaurants are within walking distance.

comment: You presumably must be a student, staff member, parent, or other member of the school community.
